To be part of the San Francisco Bay Area business community is a fantastic experience. You get easy access to all the resources that allow your company to grow and make its presence felt in the city and beyond. However, it's important to tap into the right opportunities to reap the benefits. If you want to highlight your business and expand its reach to local and global audiences, this is perhaps the best time to opt for aerial videos. San Francisco's stunning landscape and skyline offer the perfect backdrop for capturing an aerial view. However, this process is not easy. The region includes no-fly zones, airports, and protected parks that can be accessed only with proper permits. Otherwise, you could soon find yourself in legal trouble.

To avoid any hassle, consider contacting experienced agencies like [Gorilla Creative](https://www.gorillacreative.com/). They can create the perfect drone videos for your needs while managing all the logistical challenges. Here is a quick overview of this aspect to help you understand why professional help is essential.

* **Federal rules for drone usage**

You cannot risk flying a drone for commercial purposes without understanding FAA Part 107, which sets the rules and permissions for this type of equipment. For example, the drone operator must hold a valid remote pilot certificate, and all drones must be registered with the Federal Aviation Administration. There is also a limit on flying height: drones cannot fly more than 400 feet above ground level. At the same time, the pilot must maintain clear visual contact with the drone at all times; flights are also permitted only during certain parts of the day. If there are any specific requirements, the agency may apply for additional authorization if feasible.

* **Drone rules in San Francisco**

Federal regulations are just one aspect of drone video production. Local permissions must also be obtained for videos filmed with drones. Operators must secure a UAS Filming Permit for drone operations and purchase liability insurance. You also need to submit drone registration, certificates, and other essential documents. Additionally, authorities must be informed about launch locations, flight routes, height, and duration.

In some cases, neighborhood notification is also required. The permit process can take approximately 5 to 10 days to complete. Without comprehensive planning, it can be impossible to complete the desired task. Since agencies are typically well-versed in these matters, you don't have to handle this yourself; they manage everything as part of their videography services.

* **Other important areas to consider**

Shooting a drone video requires thorough planning and preparation. For example, experts can scout suitable locations for your video theme, addressing potential safety concerns and obstacles that may arise. Their knowledge of coastal weather conditions gives them greater control over when to film and what precautions to take. They can also choose the best time based on lighting conditions and identify proper launch and landing zones.

Whether you want a video to cover an event or a celebration, drones can capture everything perfectly, including the size of the crowd and the location. Drone videos can also support corporate marketing and recruitment efforts. You can showcase facilities, campuses, and operations to new employees and partners. In fact, non-profits can use this type of video to promote their fieldwork.
